ds to be updated to at least `net472` or newer. xUnit v3 requires at least .NET 6 or .NET Framework 4.7.2. Actually, let me check - xUnit v3 dropped support for .NET Framework entirely. It requires .NET 6+. Let me update to `net8.0`.\n\n2. **Package references**: \n   - `xunit` v2.9.3 → `xunit.v3` (the v3 package)\n   - `xunit.runner.visualstudio` needs to be updated to the v3 version or replaced with the new test runner\n   - `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` may still be needed depending on the runner choice\n\n3. **Test code**: The `Xunit` namespace and core attributes like `[Fact]` remain compatible in v3, though I should verify if any assertion methods have changed. The main API is largely backward compatible.\n\n4. **Test runner configuration**: xUnit v3 switched to Microsoft.Testing.Platform by default instead of VSTest, so the global.json and runner setup will need adjustment.\n\nLooking at the specific v3 migration path: the package name changes from `xunit` to `xunit.v3`, and the runner dependencies shift significantly. The v3 tests become executable assemblies rather than libraries, so I'll need to add `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` to the project file. The target framework requirement also tightens to `net6.0` or later with no .NET Framework support.\n\nFor the test code itself, the using statements and attributes like `[Fact]` remain unchanged, and the assertion syntax stays the same. The main structural difference is that the project needs to be executable rather than a test library that external runners invoke. Let me start implementing these changes.","outputTokens":1289,"requestId":"A043:1CE233:1B4B79F:1ECD6FC:69FE9258"},"id":"2fb57319-63af-4672-9a36-7ffe27ffa32d","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:48:29.306Z","parentId":"7189a9f4-8bbc-4a65-9712-e977b85ded6e"}
